Commentary: First ball of the day and England are underway straightaway! Roach starts with a full ball just outside off, Burns looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside half of the bat towards mid-wicket and the batters take a single.
Very full ball way outside off, left alone by Sibley. Not much movement for Roach yet.
Again way outside off by Roach, Sibley is not in the mood to go after it.
Third ball in a row which is outside off by Roach, Sibley shuffles a bit towards the off side but lets the ball through to Dowrich.

Almost a mix-up! This time Roach tries to attack the stumps but bowls it just outside off, Sibley flicks this one towards mid-wicket. Campbell from square leg moves across and dives to stop the ball. Burns was on his bike but Sibley sent him back just in time. Not what England need right now!

OUT! LBW! That is a big, big wicket for West Indies and what a start for the West Indies! Roach this time is successful in attacking the stumps, bowls it on a good length, angling in a bit to the right-hander. Sibley looks to flick this towards mid-wicket but is wrapped on the pads. Roach and West Indies put in a whole-hearted appeal and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Sibley, who got such a good century in the last Test, departs in the first over in this one. England in trouble early on!
Gabriel starts with a length deliver on the pads, Burns flicks it to backward square leg.
Length ball outside off, Burns leaves it alone.
Good stop and there is a lot of noise from West Indies payers. They look up for it today. On the pads, Burns flicks it, Brooks at short leg ducks and the ball hits him on his right knee.
Landed outside off, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Length delivery on off, Burns punches it through covers and gets a couple to end the over.
Very full on off, Root defends it.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Fuller delivery around off, Root gets on his front foot and drives it stylishly but finds the man at cover.
The English skipper is off the mark!  Fuller on middle and leg, Root flicks it through mid-wicket and gets three as the fielder cleans it up.
Good length ball outside off, Burns leaves it alone.
Roach offers width outside off and tempts Burns to drive but he opts against it.
Good length delivery on off, it shapes away a bit. Burns looks to defend it with soft hands but the ball goes towards gully off the outer half of his bat.
Length delivery outside off, Root lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball coming in from outside off, Root is aware of his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
Another one outside off, tempting Root to drive and also testing his knowledge of his off stump, Root is not tempted to have a feel of this delivery and leaves it alone.
This time he is beaten. On a length outside off, Joe looks to defend but the ball straightens a touch and beats him.

Root escapes an LBW verdict! Excellent bowling from West Indies so far. The lines and lengths have been really immaculate. This is just behind a length, outside off and Root looks to defend. The ball pitches and then comes back in sharply. Now, smart that Root is, he keeps his bat behind the pad, as if showing that he is playing a shot. But he is actually isn't. However, the umpire feels that he is playing a shot. So he feels the impact is outside off and gives it not out. West Indies refer it upstairs and even the third umpire feels that the impact is outside off. Hence, the review is turned down. Was Joe playing a shot?
Around middle and leg, Joe misses his flick and the ball goes off his pads towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
Outside off, on a length, a play and a miss.
Outside off, let through to the keeper.
Landed outside off, on a length, Joe looks to play inside the line and gets beaten.
Down the leg side, a flick shot is missed.
Full and around middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
A bouncer, on middle, Burns ducks.
Full and around middle, Burns looks to flick but then gets squared up. The result is a leading edge to mid off.
Sprayed down the leg side, Rory misses his flick.
Around off, Burns looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards cover.
On middle and leg, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.

FOUR BYES! Wild delivery. Miles down the leg side, on a length, Burns looks to flick but cannot reach. Poor Dowrich cannot reach either, even with a full-length dive. The ball races to the fine leg fence.
Ohhh movement. Plenty. On a length, outside off, Root feels for it but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, well defended.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Fullish and around off, well kept out.
Full and well outside off, almost outside the pitch, left alone.
Down the leg side, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Short of a length delivery on leg, Burns pulls it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length and outside off, Rory offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Burns defends it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Burns tucks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on middle, Burns defends it.
On the stumps, Burns blocks it.
On the pads, Burns turns it to the on side.
Holder continues to keep it tight and disciplined in and around the stumps. Burns shows respect and blocks it.
Length ball around off, Rory defends it.
On a good length on off, Rory defends it out.
Good length ball around off, Root looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
Roach goes full this time. Root gets behind the ball and blocks it.
Length ball which comes in from off and middle, Root glances it behind square on the leg side.
Full on off, Burns lunges forward and looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes behind square on the leg side and he takes a single.
Outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Length delivery outside off, Root shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on  off and middle, Rory defends it.
On the pads, Burns tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good ball! Good length delivery pitching on off and shapes away a bit. Root looks to defend but the ball sneaks past the outside edge.
On a good length and outside off, Root lets it go.
Good length delivery outside off, Joe offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Root looks to drive but misses it.
On a good length and outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Good shot! Length delivery on off, Burns punches it through covers for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Burns keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Rory blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it towards mid on.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
On a good length and outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on leg, Root looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
On a length on middle, Root flicks it through square leg for a run.
Length delivery on middle, Burns flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
On a good length on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Cornwall starts with a shorter delivery on off, Burns punches it to cover.
Slower through the air on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Darted on the pads, Burns flicks it to the on side and gets a couple.
Tossed up on off, Burns defends it.
Beauty! Cornwall gives this air and turns the ball off the good part of the surface from around off. Burns looks to defend but misses.
Floated on off, Burns blocks it to get through the over. Tidy first over from Cornwall.
On a length on off, Root plays it to point.
Good length delivery on off, Root defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Joe leaves it alone.
Goes right back and blocks.
Tossed up, around off, well pushed out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Shorter around off, Burns cuts it but finds point.
Cornwall gives it air on off, Burns looks to defend but it goes behind square on the off side off the outer half of his bat and gets a couple.
On the pads, Burns turns it to the on side.
Floated on off, Burns lunges forward and blocks it.
Tossed up around off, Burns looks to defend but the ball turns away and squares Burns up.
Short delivery outside off, Root lets it go.
Good length delivery outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Root drives it through mid off. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Root defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Joe leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Root pushes it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Short delivery down the leg side, Root looks to pull but misses it.
Floated delivery on off, Root guides it towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
Loopy delivery on middle, Root plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Flighted delivery on middle, Burns defends it off the back foot.
On off, Burns guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Rory blocks it well.
On a length on middle, Root flicks it through square leg for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Burns blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Short delivery outside off, Burns looks to cut but misses it.
Play and a miss! Full and outside off, Burns looks to drive but misses it.
Holder bowls it down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Root defends it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Root defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Root drives it towards covers for a single.
On middle, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Burns flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Root looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
On a length on off, Burns pushes it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it towards mid on where the fielder does well to stop it. The batsmen still manage to take a single.
Full delivery on off, Root plays it to point.
On a length on middle, Root flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Short delivery down the leg side, Root looks to pull but misses it.
Good length delivery outside off, Joe offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery just outside off, Burns looks to defend but misses it.
Floated delivery on middle, Burns comes down the track and blocks it well.

OUT! Run Out! Excellent work in the field from and Root who was getting in his groove has to depart. Big wicket for the tourists and a big blow for Enngland. Back-to-back run out for Joe Root. The last one was a sacrfice not this time. Floated delivery on off, Burns looks to defend but the ball goes to the right of short third man. Root calls for a quick single and goes for it. Chase gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end. The ball kisses the bail. Root stretches but does not dive. The West Indies players are up in celebration. The umpire goes to the T.V. umpire help. Replay rolls in and shows that the ball kissed the bail and dislodged them and when that happened the English skipper was short of his crease. Had it not been a direct hit, Root would have survived. Just when Joe Root was getting along his innings has been cut short. Brilliant work from Roston Chase! He has had a terrific series in all three departments. West Indies strike one more before Lunch.
Full and fired in middle, Stokes defends from his crease.
Full on middle again, Stokes plays that from the crease and gets an inside edge through square leg.
FOUR! Short and outside off, this is cut away through point.
FOUR BYES! Length delivery down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses it. The ball swings late and it causes Dowrich to miss it as well. The ball goes towards the fence for four byes.
Length delivery down the leg side, Stokes lets it go.
Outside off, left alone.
On a good length on off, Stokes looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It falls short of the second slip fielder.
Length delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Stokes plays it towards covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Stokes blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ben keeps it out.
Cornwall bowls it down the leg side, Stokes lets it go.
On middle, Stokes looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
A bouncer now, on middle, Burns ducks.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the back foot.
In the air but safe! Short ball around the body, Burns looks to pull but mistimes it and it goes high in the air. Luckily for him it falls short of the man coming from fine leg.
Good length delivery outside off, Stokes offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Ben blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Stokes keeps it out.

Loopy delivery on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Nice use of the feet! Tossed up delivery on middle, Stokes comes down the track and drives it through mid on for a boundary.
On middle, Stokes defends it out.
Length delivery down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses it.
Gabriel bowls a bouncer, Burns does well to duck under it.
Gabriel again bowls a bumper, Rory ducks under it.
Bouncer on leg, Burns does well to duck under it.
On a good length on off, Burns looks to defend  but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
On a length on middle, Burns flicks it through square leg for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!

FOUR! The new session starts with a boundary! Holder starts with a loosener as he bowls a length delivery outside off. Burns gets on his back foot and punches it through backward point for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it towards mid off.
On a good length on off, Burns looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It falls short of the gully fielder.
On a good length on middle, Burns looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Length delivery on off, Burns gets on his front foot and drives it through covers and gets a couple to end the over.
On a length on middle, Stokes flicks it through square leg for a run.
Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it towards mid on.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Rory looks to drive but misses it.

Full delivery on middle, Burns plays it to mid on.

Good length delivery outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Ben defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Burns lets it go.

Full delivery on off, Burns drives it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.

Roach bowls a bouncer, Burns does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery outside off, Rory shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Stokes pushes through covers and gets a couple.
Bouncer on the body, Stokes pulls it through mid-wicket and gets a single
Another short ball, Burns pulls it through mid-wicket. The fielder stops the ball before the ropes and saves a run.
Fuller on off, Stokes plays it to mid off and takes a single.
Fuller on off, Burns defends it.
Good length delivery on the body, Stokes tucks it to the leg side.
Full on off, Stokes defends it a bit late so the ball bounces around him and hits him on his back pad.
On the body, Stokes turns it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Fuller on off, Burns blocks it.
On the pads, Rory turns it to the on side.
Once again Roach delivers it on middle and leg, closer to Burns' body and this time he glances it behind square on the leg side and keeps the strike with a single.
Full and outside off, Burns goes back and pushes it towards cover.
Comes down the track this time, gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks.
Going on the back foot this time, working it behind square on the leg side for one more.
Around middle, Stokes goes back and works it to the leg side for a single.
Full once more, nicely tossed up, pushed back watchfully.
A proper solid backfoot defense, as the over ends.
On a length, around middle, Stokes rises with the bounce and pushes it to the leg side.

HOWZZAT? Nope, says the umpire. Roach is not sure. Jason Holder asks his slip fielders and his keeper. No one is sure either. So no review. A short ball, around off, Stokes looked to pull but was hurried into the shot. Extra pace from Roach. The ball went off something to the keeper and there was a noise. There was a mild appeal but nothing much in it. The ball hit the helmet.
FOUR! No stopping that. Short ball but Ben is ready. Camps back and pulls it with disdain through mid-wicket. Bring 'em on!
Good length ball, watchfully defended.
Full and wide outside off, the tempter, left alone.

OUT! BOWLED! Stokes stands in disbelief. What happened? A ball has gone through the gate. Massive gap between bat and pad. Kaboom! On a length, just outside off, Stokes looks to defend but a bit lazily. There is no foot movement but the ball moves. There is a big gap between bat and pad and the ball finds that. Off and middle pegs hit. Stokes is a goner!
Full to begin with, around off, Burns blocks it in front of short leg.
Faster, around middle, tucked straight to short leg again.
Less flight this time, around off, pushed to the off side.
Aha... use of the feet. Burns dances down and pushes it towards mid on.
Oohhh... a bit aerial, but just wide of short leg! Full and on the pads, Rory looks to flick but gets it off the inner half. Just past short leg!
Full and straight, well blocked out. Nice complimenting over from Cornwall. Nothing adventurous. This means Roach will have the new man on strike.
Easy. Just too easy. New man, get a straight ball. What do I need to do? Flick it away and I am underway. A single to square leg.
That is a shocker. Full and miles outside off, Rory does not even need to play that. Nearly outside the pitch! Roach is letting away some momentum go.
Outside off, Burns watchfully lets it go. This was a lot closer than the previous one.
Fuller in length, around off, well kept out.
On a length, outside off, moving away, shouldered arms to.
A fine ball to end the over. Fullish and just straightening a touch, RB defends it watchfully. A maiden over but really not of much use from Roach. A bit too wayward.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Around off, Pope comes down the track and pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
Flatter, around off, Ollie goes back to block again.
Similar ball, same defensive stroke from Pope.
The use of the feet again. Pope dances out and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Decent shot. Quicker one, fired in with the arm, Pope goes back and punches it past first slip. That fielder himself has to run all the way towards third man. John Campbell it is. Three runs taken.

Another one on the helmet. The umpire is in Pope's ears. Excellent short ball from Roach. This is around off, Ollie looks to pull but is beaten by pace. The ball rockets onto the helmet and then deflects towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
Another bouncer, this time to a different batsman. Burns ducks under it calmly.
There comes the sucker ball. Full and outside off. Asking to be driven. Is driven, but with proper footwork. Straight to cover.
Full and outside off again, but this time Rory gets across and pokes it into the leg side. Towards mid-wicket where there is a yawning gap. Easy couple taken.
Fractionally shorter than full, outside off, but a touch wide. RB lets it pass.
Aahhh... nearly! Full and miles wide outside off, Burns almost goes after it. The thought is there for the drive but then, he bails out, at the last moment. The slip cordon is cheering on Roach.
Full and outside off, not much pace, watchfully defended.

Now Pope comes down the track and works it through mid-wicket. Poor fielding from Roston Chase. He ambles after the ball and the batsmen spot that. There is a fumble as well near the ropes and the batsmen take the third on the throw.
Shorter, outside off, played straight to point.

Fuller and pushed towards point. Chase is the fielder again and England think about the single and get it. Hang on. Here is the reason. While fielding the ball, Chase got an extra bounce. Hence fumbled. That would have stung him on his arm.
Flatter outside off, watchfully kept out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On a good length, around off, well pushed to the off side.
Fullish and around off, pushed towards cover.

This time Burns walks into the stroke. Normally, batsmen do this to negate the swing. There isn't any but this is just Burns' habit. Every now and then, he will step out. This is pushed towards mid on.
There comes the response from the fast bowler. I am no military medium guy, so better don't step out! A bumper, a sharp one at that, around leg, Burns is forced to duck. Try walking into that one...
Comes around the wicket, does Gabriel, dishes it into the ribs, but Burns tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
FOUR! Bit of a gift after the break. Short and outside off, easy for feasting and Burns feasts. Rocks back and cuts it through the covers.
Fuller and straighter, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Looped up, around off, Rory stretches out to defend.
Around middle, pushed to the leg side.
Around middle again, Burns goes back and blocks.
A length ball, outside off, Pope stays back and defends. The ball rolls to the off side and the batsmen take a single.
A short ball, outside off, Burns slashes hard but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces in front of the keeper.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Beaten! Excellent from Gabriel. Full and around leg, Burns looks to defend but the ball pitches and then moves away off the seam to beat the outside edge.
Full and just outside off, well defended.
On a good length, defended watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! That is a solid shot. Full and outside off, Pope comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Around middle, defended solidly.
Floated outside off, Ollie comes down the track and pushes it to the leg side for a single.
Around off, well defended.
Outside off, punched off the back foot, through point for a couple.
Full and around middle and off, Pope works it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.

That is a jaffa. On a length outside off, Pope looks to defend but the ball comes back in a long way and nearly shaves the off stump. Ollie thought he had it covered but the ball exposed the tiniest of gaps between bat and pad.
Outside off, left alone.
A bit too straight, flicked away for a single.
A bouncer now, on middle, Burns ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Pope defends this solidly.
Fired in, outside off, Ollie defends watchfully.
Around off, OP blocks it out again.
Goes right back in his crease and defends.
Full and around off, Pope comes down the track and flicks it uppishly, wide of short mid-wicket, for a single.
Short and outside off, Rory goes back and cuts it towards point.
A length ball, outside off, solidly defended.
A short ball, around off, Pope lets it go.
A short ball, around off, pulled through square leg for a single.
Around middle and leg, helped through square leg for one more.
Wild. Ill-directed. Full and miles down the leg side, Pope tries his best to flick. Misses. Shane Dowrich dives to his left to collect.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Burns reaches out and drives it towards cover.
Around middle, watchfully defended.
Rory comes down the track and pushes it towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sir Andrew Strauss, Chase heard you! And dear Cornwall, what a catch! What a catch! Will come back to that Strauss comment later. First, the ball. Short and outside off, Burns rocks back to cut but is too close to the ball. He gets a thick outside edge as a result and the ball flies thick and fast to first slip. The giant Rahkeem Cornwall there, has barely any time to react but he trusts his instincts. He just thrusts his right hand and the ball sticks! Tremendous reflexes. Chase is ringing the bells again, as his celebration suggests. Now, about the Strauss comment. Sir Andrew Strauss on air, felt that after including an extra spinner in your side, you should not be bowling first. He was just saying 'Hmmmm...' pondering over something else to say when Chase struck. Poor from Burns. Should have carried on!
How did that miss the off stump? Full and flighted outside off, Buttler looks to drive but the ball spins in, goes beneath the bat and goes over the off stump!
Around middle, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Around off, pushed towards point.

The wobbly seam is troubling Shane Dowrich again. He was all at sea in the second Test and being on the field for a long time did not assist him. A length ball, outside off, Ollie lets it go. The ball wobbles off the seam and then moves in a long way. Dowrich struggles to collect and fumbles, conceding a bye.
A bouncer now, Buttler ducks.
Another bouncer, the result is the same.
A length ball, outside off, Jos looks to defend but the ball cuts back in, rises steeply, makes Buttler hop, takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Around off, defended watchfully this time.
Full and around off, Pope defends it watchfully.
On a length outside off, Ollie is solid in defense again.
Full and outside off, Pope pushes this through the covers and gets a couple.
Full and down the leg side, Ollie misses his flick.
A length ball, around off, OP defends it watchfully.
A length ball, outside off, Pope gets across and shoulders arms.

Na na... not what Holder or Gabriel had in mind. He needed the new man on strike. He looks back at the pitch, as if to indicate something to do with his landing. Full and fast yes, but straying down the leg side. Buttler tickles it towards fine leg for a single.
Outside off, pushed towards point.

Poor shot and poor keeping again. Seems like a loss in confidence for Dowrich. Full and wide outside off, Pope looks at that and cannot resist himself. Throws the kitchen sink at it, looking to drive but misses. Shane Dowrich looks to collect to his right, but struggles against the wobbly seam. Fumbles.
Back of a length, outside off, Ollie hops and defends.
Outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Landed outside off, on a length, Jos shoulders arms.

WOULD POPE HAVE BEEN A GONER? Dear me, he would have been! On middle, Ollie pushes it towards mid on and sets off for a single. It is Roston Chase at short mid-wicket who ambles towards the ball, stoops to pick the ball up and at that time, Pope is gone for all money. Because he is just halfway down the track. But, just when he is about to flick the ball with his left hand, he fumbles the ball and it pops out. What a relief for Ollie Pope.
Around off, solidly defended.
Fuller this time, well defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller in length, outside off, watchfully defended.
Wider outside off, let through again.
Around off, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.

Umm... leaving? Playing? Perhaps caught in two minds. On a length outside off, Buttler looks to defend initially but then thinks to let the ball go. Is late and the bat is left hanging in the air. Luckily for him, the ball hits the good spot of the willow and goes on the bounce to the slip cordon.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Fuller in length, around off, flicked towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, kept out watchfully to the off side. A quick single taken.
Wide outside off, just holds its line, doesn't swing back in, good from Buttler as he doesn't chase that. Leaves it through. TEA ON DAY 1!
False start to the new session from Holder. He starts the final session with a delivery down the leg side. Pope looks to flick but it is too far away.
Holder finds his line and bowls it on a length on off, Pope defends it off the front foot.
Holder hits the deck hard on off, Pope gets on his back foot and dabs the ball down the ground.
Slightly fuller and shaping away, Pope defends it from right under his eyeline.
Full on off, Pope taps it back to Holder.
Maiden to begin the new session. Good length ball on off, Ollie defends it to get through the over.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Jos defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on middle, Buttler pulls it through square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Pope blocks it off the back foot.

Edged but falls shot! Good length ball outside off, it is in the channel of uncertainty. Pope lunges forward and has a feel of the ball. The ball takes the outside edge and falls short of Holder at second slip.
On middle and leg, Pope flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple as he gets off the mark for the session.
On a good length and outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Buttler punches it to covers.
Good length delivery outside off, Jos offers no shot to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Pope looks to defend but misses it.
Length delivery on off, Ollie plays it to covers.
On a good length and outside off, Pope leaves it alone.

OUT! Caught! Broad strikes in his first over and West Indies have lost their first wicket. This is the reason you give the new ball to Broad because he makes things happen. Good length delivery on off, it shapes away just a bit. Brathwaite looks to defend to protect the off pole but the ball takes an outside edge and goes straight to first slip. The England skipper standing at first slip makes no mistake and takes a good catch.

Appeal but turned down by the umpire. Length ball pitching on off and angling in. Hope looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads. Broad and his teammates go up in appeal but the umpire turns it down.

EDGED AND DROPPED! It is Ben Stokes out of all the people who has dropped it. Shows he is human after all. He will be gutted to have dropped this one. It is an easy one and he knows it as well. Good length ball around off and it moves away a tad. Campbell looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the right of second slip. Ben Stokes there moves to his right but the ball goes in and comes out of his hand. He is shattered as we all know he sets a very high benchmark for himself. Anderson cannot believe it that he has not had his first victim today.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh, the master, the master, Jimmy is the master! You feel it will come this way but it goes the other way. You feel it will go the other way but it says knock knock, hello! Sensational from Jimmy. He sets Brooks up with a couple of outswingers and then gets this one to swing In. Shamarh is caught off guard, as he fails to pick the shine on the ball. Plays for the outswinger but has to adjust late for the inswinger. Too late. Inside edge is taken and Buttler does the rest. Up goes the finger on the appeal. What a setup. Terrific.

EDGED, SHORT! Playing with soft hands is the key. Full and outside off, Chase commits into the defense but not completely. It is a mere push, more of a dead-bat, so that even if it is an outside edge, it won't carry behind. And it doesn't. Ben Stokes at second slip cannot quite get his hands to stop the ball and it goes past him. Two runs taken.

Good running. Chase works this through mid-wicket. Broad gets there from long leg, beating Bess from mid-wicket. He looks to slide but slips instead. Stumbles but manages to stop the ball. Three runs taken.
A length ball, nearing the rib cage, Blackwood looks to fend it off but misses and is hit on the body. He is pretty uncomfortable with that length and there is Ollie Pope waiting, at leg gully.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

OUT! LBW! More success for Stuart Broad. Huge smile on his face. Chase departs and the West Indies are 5 down. That looked as plumb as it could get. The nip-backer, as it is always called when Stewy bowls. On a length, outside off, Chase looks to stay back and defend. But the ball nips back in and stays low a touch as well. This is just Day 2, so cannot really blame Chase for playing back. Hits Chase on the knee roll as he misses his defense and there is an appeal. Not from Broad. He celebrates first, then as if like an obligation, turns back and asks umpire Kettleborough, who already has his finger up. Now now, Stewy, you don't want to be spending the evening in dad's office, do you? As per the rule, a bowler needs to appeal before celebrating, if it involves the decision of the umpire. Remember, the great Glenn McGrath being warned, around 15 years back for not appealing? Coming to this ball, Ball Tracker shows it to be clipping the bails.

FOUR BYES! Tough luck for Jos Buttler. On a length, outside off, Holder lets it go. But the ball comes back in a long way and seams past the off stump. Buttler dives to his left but cannot stop it. The ball races to the fine leg fence.

On a length, outside off, watchfully defended.
Leaving? Playing? Indecision. On a length outside off, Holder looks to defend initially but then decides to take his bat off. Is late and the ball goes off the bottom edge, on the bounce, to gully.

And again! Jason needs to decide a bit quicker if he wants to leave the ball. Full and outside off, stays low, JH looks to defend, then tries to bail out, only to get a bottom edge on the bounce to the keeper.
FOUR LEG BYES. Taking evasive action there. A short ball, around middle, the skipper looks to duck but the ball hits his chest and goes to the fine leg fence.
Back of a length, around off, watchfully blocked out.
FOUR! Nice timing. Full and around middle, Holder whips it through mid-wicket and finds the fence.

NOT OUT PLUS 5 RUNS! Full and outside off, Holder pushes it towards mid-wicket and sets off for a single. Dom Sibley gets across to his left, picks the ball up, turns and has a shy at the bowler's end. The ball hits the stumps and then deflects past the man backing up at mid off to the long off fence. Ben Stokes from second slip believes it is gone but replays show otherwise. Holder is comfortably in.
Around off, blocked from the crease.

This is bowled from Chris Woakes a bit wide from the stumps and it comes back in to ping Holder in front of the stumps. The umpire disagrees to the LBW shout but England and Joe Root take the review. Ball Tracker comes in and shows the ball to be going over the stumps. England still have 2 reviews in the bag and not too much to worry on that front.

Replay rolls in and shows Holder is in safely.

CAUGHT OFF A NO BALL! Big moment in this Test. Woakes has overstepped his line by just and Holder gets a lifeline. Woakes bowls a length ball around the body, Holder looks to flick but it does not come off the middle and ends up hitting it upishly to the right of short mid-wicket. Ollie Pope there dives to his right and takes a very good catch. Holder stays to see whether Woakes has overstepped his line or not. Replay rolls and it finds Chris Woakes guilty. Holder knows he is a goner but decides to signal the 'T'. Ultra Edge first rolls in and it shows that there is no bat involved. Time for the all-important Ball Tracker and it shows all reds. The West Indies skipper has to walk back and he takes away a review with him as well.

It goes towards first slip where Hope tries to take the catch but it bounces in front of him. It is referred upstairs. Replays show that it bounced in front of him.

FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Root pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Holder bowls a bouncer outside off, Root lets it sail through to the keeper.

FOUR more to Root. Blackwood is quick. Exceptionally quick in the outfield. But this was timed so sweetly by Root that it beat him. Full and outside off, Joe gets down and sweeps it powerfully, yet beautifully through mid-wicket. The ball races towards the fence, beating Jermaine Blackwood's dive to his right.

SIX! England have shifted gears and the skipper has put on some dancing shoes. Excellent footwork. Root comes down the track and smashes this tossed up ball over long off for a biggie.

That's beaten everything. Shorter off sinner pitching on leg, Root looks to punch it on the off side but the ball spins and goes between his bat and pad and it also misses the stumps and goes behind. They steal two byes.
Floated on off, Root blocks it.
Flighted on off, Root sweeps it through mid-wicket and gets a single to move to 48.
On the pads, RB flicks it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Floated on off, Root sweeps it to deep mid-wicket and gets a single to move to 49. 11 off the over and the lead is now 374!

FOUR! Root reaches his fifty in style. 49th Test fifty for the England skipper and he has got that with a glorious shot. Length ball around off, Root comes down the track and smacks it over mid off for a boundary.
What is happening? Good length ball outside off, Root looks play the scoop shot but misses.
FOUR! Shorter from Roach but Root is in T20 mode so he sees the cherry as a white ball and pulls it through mid-wicket for another boundary.
Yorker outside off, Root dabs it to gully.
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it towards third man and gets a couple.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Fuller outside off, Root heaves it over long on and ends the over with a boundary.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Tossed up delivery on middle, Burns lofts it over mid on for a boundary.

Short delivery on off, Burns lofts it over point for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Burns fails to get to his century! Tossed up delivery on off, Burns looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It goes towards the substitute keeper where Joshua Da Silva takes a comfortable catch. ENGLAND HAVE DECLARED WITH A LEAD OF 398!
Anderson starts with a good length delivery around off. A hint of away moment but Brathwaite gets behind it and blocks it.
Good length ball outside off this time, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Fuller around off, the ball looks to have kept a tad low. Brathwaite manages to get his bat down in time.
Length delivery outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
On the pads, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Maiden to begin with. Good length ball on off, Brathwaite defends it.
Broad starts with a fuller delivery to the southpaw on off, Campbell pushes it to point and looks for a single which was never existent.
Good length ball angling in to the left-hander, Campbell manages to defend it.

OUT! Caught! Broad gets his 498th Test victim and that comes from a beauty! Traditional Broad wicket. He has enjoyed bowling to left-handers and has more often than not won the battle against them. Nothing different here. Terrific delivery from Broad. He comes in and bowls it slightly fuller on off, Campbell thinks it will come with the angle but goes the other way. It takes the fat outside edge of his willow and goes straight to first slip. Skipper, Joe Root there makes no mistake and takes a relatively easy catch. Just the start England would have wanted. Nightmare beginning to the chase for the Caribbean nation.
Shorter from Broad! Roach looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of his bat and goes to the off side allowing him to get off the mark.
Length delivery on off, Brathwaite pushes it to point and gets to the other end.
On the pads, Roach flicks it to the leg side and gets a couple to end the over.

OUT! Caught behind! Two wickets in no time for Broad and make that victim number 499 for him in Tests. He was angry on being dropped from  the first Test and he has guided that anger in the right place. The night watchman does not survive the day to see the night. Excellent delivery. It would be good for majority of the top order batsmen, it was going to be too good for the night watchman. Broad bowls it full around off and the ball shapes away a bit. Roach looks to defend but the ball kisses his outside edge and goes straight into the mitts of Buttler. Can he end the day now with wicket no. 500?
On the pads, Hope flicks it to mid-wicket to start his innings.
Outside off, Hope leaves it alone.

Almost had scalp number 500. Peach of a delivery from Broad. He comes wide of the crease and makes the ball straightens after pitching. Hope looks to defend but gets nothing on it and the ball misses the outside edge just by a mere inch.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on off, Hope looks to defend but does so with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through gully for a boundary. Hope is off the mark but not in a conventional manner.

Fuller on off, Hope pushes it to mid on.

Extra bounce! Broad hits the deck hard and the ball shoots off the surface. Hope hops and takes his eyes off the ball but somehow manages to defend it.
Full on off, Hope defends it. One ball to go. Can Hope survive or will  Broad end the day with 500 Test wickets?
Hope survives! Good length ball outside off, Hope looks to defend but misses. That is STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Starts with a ball on the pads, Brathwaite gets across and tucks it towards leg gully.
Full and outside off, pushed solidly towards short extra cover.
Ooohh... this stays low, landing just outside off, Kraigg shuffles across and blocks.
Beauty. On a length outside off, KB looks to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge. Guess Brathwaite needs to be positive. Try and score runs, rather than just looking to defend every ball.

Brathwaite looks to defend but misses and gets hit low on the back foot. Broad and his teammates go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. That was as plumb as It could get and Brathwaite has a rare double. 583 balls left in the day, 7 wickets to defend...

West Indies in big trouble here and have lost both their overnight batsmen. Woakes gets into the wicket column. Woakes bowls it slightly shorter outside off, Hope looks to pull it but ends up hitting it off the upper half of his bat. The ball goes high in the air in front of mid off. Three players are coming for it but Broad wants to be part of the action so he calls it out loudly. He keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a good catch. Hope's struggle in the longest format continues and there will be a lot of questions asked and he will have to retrospect and think, was that shot really necessary?
Good length delivery on off, Brooks keeps it out.

Brooks looks to drive it towards mid on but without any foot movement and away from his body. The ball shapes in and kisses the inside edge as it goes low to the left of Buttler. He takes an easy catch behind the stumps. Looks like the only way West Indies can save this Test match is by looking up at the skies but at the moment they are not helping the tourists.

OUT! Run Out! The last thing West Indies needed was a run out and that is what has happened here. Excellent work from Dom Bess! Good length delivery on off, Blackwood plays it towards point and looks for a single. There is a bit of hesitation but they decide to go for it. Bess at backward point runs to his right, gets to the ball and turns. He has to score a direct hit as Buttler has not reached the stumps and Bess does hit the stumps. Excellent from the spinner. Chase is well short of his crease and the umpire does not even go upstairs. Chase does not look back and continues his walk to the pavillion. Brilliant from Bess, he has not had much to do but he has shown his concentration and has done a job when called upon albeit in the field.
Length ball on off, Holder blocks it.
Full and outside off, Holder gets a big stride forward and blocks.
Around off, this is defended from the crease.

Again, a tight single. Full and outside off, Holder pushes this wide of mid off and sets off. The fielder takes a little bit of time to release the ball but even then, Holder looked to be in trouble. The throw misses the stumps at the bowler's end.
Fuller on off, Holder pushes it to mid off.
Bowled with a cross-seam, on a length, outside off, Holder feels for the ball but is beaten due to the late inward movement.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, Blackwood blocks it with a dead bat.
On off, defended by JB.
Bouncer to end the over. It is around the body and Blackwood does well to hop and block.

NOT OUT! Daylight between bat and pad and LBW was never in contention to be fair. On the leg side, Holder looks to flick but the ball clips something and goes to Buttler. Woakes and Buttler go up in appeal but the umpire turns it down. Root decide to gamble and take the review. Replay rolls in  and shows that the ball just clipped the thigh pad and not the bat as the willow was nowhere in the frame. Ball Tracker comes as a formality and shows that the ball is missing leg pole by miles.

OUT! LBW! Holder did not get any bat on it and it is plumb in front. West Indies' skipper and best batter departs and the tourists are falling like nine pins. Good length ball pitching on off and middle and nipping back in. Holder looks to play it straight but misses and gets hit on the pads. Woakes and co. go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Holder decides to signal the 'T' straightaway. Only an inside edge could probably save him there. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes and brings bad news for Holder as it shows three reds. The skipper departs and along with him goes the tiny tinker of Caribbean hopes of survival.

NOT OUT! No spike as the ball goes past the bat on Ultra Edge and England lose another review. Strange review from Root in the first place as there was no noise and neither was Archer too interested. Good length ball outside off, Blackwood looked to drive but the ball went behind and Buttler and Root started celebrating. The umpire was unmoved, Archer too was not in it. Root though straightaway signalled the 'T'. Replay rolled in and Ultra Edge had a flat line as the ball passed the bat. Waste of a review.

Picked up from where Broad left off. Fuller around off and nipping back in, Dowrich moves across and looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on the pads. The England players go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Dowrich does not even consider about the review and follows the marching orders.

Appeal for LBW and the umpire gives Cornwall his marching order. He too does not review and walks to the pavilion.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is all over! Short of a length delivery on leg, Blackwood looks to pull but gets a faint edge. It goes towards the keeper where Jos Buttler dives to his left and takes a good catch. ENGLAND WIN THE MATCH BY 269 RUNS AND WIN THE SERIES 2-1!
